00:25:53,640 --> 00:25:55,840
Let's sit you down. Come on, that's it.

260
00:25:56,760 --> 00:25:57,760
All right.

261
00:25:58,600 --> 00:25:59,920
A nice sit-down.

262
00:26:01,400 --> 00:26:02,400
There.

263
00:26:05,280 --> 00:26:06,360
Mum?

264
00:26:07,080 --> 00:26:08,320
Look at me.

265
00:26:12,160 --> 00:26:14,520
Er...
Where's Dr Ellis now?

266
00:26:14,600 --> 00:26:15,960
He's with another patient.

267
00:26:17,480 --> 00:26:18,720
Of course he is.

268
00:26:20,440 --> 00:26:22,480
What's changed?
What are you giving her?

269
00:26:23,200 --> 00:26:24,840
Same dosage.

270
00:26:24,920 --> 00:26:26,680
She may have built up a tolerance.

271
00:26:27,520 --> 00:26:29,440
We need to look into options.

272
00:26:30,120 --> 00:26:31,520
Where's the picture?

273
00:26:32,520 --> 00:26:36,640
Dr Ellis wanted to see if she was
staring at the photo or...

274
00:26:37,360 --> 00:26:39,640
just staring.

275
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:43,600
Can you put it back, please?

276
00:26:53,360 --> 00:26:54,400
Mum.

277
00:26:57,920 --> 00:26:59,000
Talk to me.

278
00:26:59,080 --> 00:27:00,720
Hey? What's happened?

279
00:27:03,040 --> 00:27:04,720
What's wrong, hmm?

280
00:27:07,920 --> 00:27:09,840
- Mum!
- Give her time.

281
00:27:10,640 --> 00:27:13,160
I've given her time.
She just keeps getting worse.

282
00:27:13,240 --> 00:27:14,640
It's this place.

283
00:27:14,720 --> 00:27:16,960
- This is the best place for her.
- Is it?

284
00:27:17,680 --> 00:27:19,120
She needs specialist care.

285
00:27:20,520 --> 00:27:22,440
If-if you want to talk to Dr Ellis...

286
00:27:22,520 --> 00:27:24,536
Dr Ellis doesn't know what's
wrong with her, none of you do.

287
00:27:24,560 --> 00:27:26,680
And you don't listen to me.
Nobody listens!

288
00:27:30,280 --> 00:27:31,640
I'm sorry. I just...

289
00:27:35,800 --> 00:27:37,760
Can you leave us, please?

290
00:27:52,560 --> 00:27:54,120
Where are you?

291
00:27:56,200 --> 00:27:57,760
Where have you gone?

292
00:27:59,480 --> 00:28:02,480
I'm not gonna let you leave me again,
do you understand?

293
00:28:03,720 --> 00:28:05,400
You have to come back.

294
00:28:10,120 --> 00:28:12,160
You have to come back.

295
00:28:41,160 --> 00:28:42,160
DI Dhillon.

296
00:28:43,520 --> 00:28:44,760
DS Boyd.

297
00:28:46,040 --> 00:28:47,280
Thanks for coming.

298
00:28:47,920 --> 00:28:49,280
It's temporary.

299
00:28:49,360 --> 00:28:51,720
Even so,
if I have to have a babysitter,

300
00:28:51,800 --> 00:28:53,600
it's nice to have someone I can bully.

301
00:28:53,680 --> 00:28:55,600
Should have just asked them
to promote you.

302
00:28:55,680 --> 00:28:58,760
Well, you...
you can take that up with my wife.

303
00:28:58,840 --> 00:29:01,880
And my 3-year-old. Plus, DI's
have to work on Sundays, so...

304
00:29:02,840 --> 00:29:04,280
You still singing in the choir?

305
00:29:05,680 --> 00:29:07,760
Badly but, you know, with feeling.

306
00:29:10,480 --> 00:29:12,960
I've cleared a desk
for you upstairs, so...

307
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:17,080
I'll grab my pass,
we'll head straight out.

308
00:29:18,400 --> 00:29:20,480
You don't wanna say some hellos?

309
00:29:21,320 --> 00:29:22,960
They don't blame you, Ravi.

310
00:29:29,200 --> 00:29:30,760
For Shepherd?

311
00:29:30,840 --> 00:29:32,040
Or for Nick?

312
00:29:34,680 --> 00:29:36,200
It's not a reunion, Sam.

313
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:39,640
Yeah. Just saying.

314
00:29:39,720 --> 00:29:40,920
Thank you.

315
00:29:41,520 --> 00:29:44,640
If it's all the same, I just wanna
get out there and put this right.

316
00:29:46,040 --> 00:29:47,360
Yes. It's your call.

317
00:29:48,960 --> 00:29:50,760
So, where do you wanna start?

318
00:29:53,800 --> 00:29:55,720
<i>Now, these cameras
belong to the school,</i>

319
00:29:55,800 --> 00:29:57,960
<i>so you need to be very careful with them.</i>

320
00:29:58,400 --> 00:29:59,520
<i>Jason Williams.</i>

321
00:30:00,080 --> 00:30:01,320
Are you listening?

322
00:30:02,040 --> 00:30:03,080
No!

323
00:30:03,160 --> 00:30:05,400
You're going to be taking
these home with you,

324
00:30:05,480 --> 00:30:09,760
which means that you are responsible
for making sure they stay in one piece.

325
00:30:09,840 --> 00:30:12,360
Martin, that goes for you too.

326
00:30:12,440 --> 00:30:15,040
Er, no, Johnny, don't do that, please.

327
00:30:15,680 --> 00:30:19,080
We're not taking pictures
of ourselves or each other.

328
00:30:19,160 --> 00:30:21,840
Can we pay attention, please?

329
00:30:21,920 --> 00:30:24,600
That goes for you too, Isaac Chambers.

330
00:30:27,200 --> 00:30:28,440
Thank you.

331
00:30:32,240 --> 00:30:35,240
I want you to take pictures of nature.

332
00:30:35,960 --> 00:30:40,640
So... animals, trees, rivers, beaches.

333
00:30:41,400 --> 00:30:43,920
But we're not just thinking about nature.

334
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:46,056
We're thinking about the effect
that people have on nature.

335
00:30:46,080 --> 00:30:48,240
I thought you all
did brilliant work on these.

336
00:30:48,320 --> 00:30:51,160
- What sort of effect does it...
- Lots of really nice ideas here.

337
00:30:51,240 --> 00:30:53,080
- Or negative...
- Simon, please pay attention.

338
00:30:53,120 --> 00:30:55,376
- I'm not gonna tell you again.
- Are we responsible or irresponsible?

339
00:30:55,400 --> 00:30:58,200
I need to talk to a few of you
about your handwriting,

340
00:30:58,280 --> 00:31:02,120
Okay. Pollution... Jason, put that down!

341
00:31:04,760 --> 00:31:07,240
Isaac, what was I just saying?

342
00:31:08,440 --> 00:31:09,920
What was I just saying?

343
00:31:12,160 --> 00:31:13,800
Is that supposed to be funny?

344
00:31:18,760 --> 00:31:19,840
What's wrong?

345
00:31:21,240 --> 00:31:22,440
Are you feeling okay?

346
00:31:32,880 --> 00:31:34,960
It's all right. It's not broken.

347
00:31:35,040 --> 00:31:36,840
Quiet, please.

348
00:31:46,080 --> 00:31:48,720
We don't wanna scare anyone.
This is all precautionary,

349
00:31:48,800 --> 00:31:51,560
but we can't ignore coincidences.

350
00:31:52,280 --> 00:31:54,160
Shepherd was a stone's throw away.

351
00:31:54,240 --> 00:31:55,920
It's possible he's planning something.

352
00:31:56,000 --> 00:31:58,360
Some of the kids come
to school through that park.

353
00:31:58,920 --> 00:32:03,120
We need to make parents aware of
the risks but without causing a panic.

354
00:32:03,200 --> 00:32:04,520
No, sure.

355
00:32:05,600 --> 00:32:06,640
Sorry, Miss.

356
00:32:07,240 --> 00:32:08,960
Sorry.

357
00:32:10,080 --> 00:32:12,360
Sorry, I... I've forgotten your name.

358
00:32:12,440 --> 00:32:14,640
DI Dhillon. Ravi.

359
00:32:15,680 --> 00:32:17,040
All good?

360
00:32:19,320 --> 00:32:21,160
Sorry. DS Boyd.

361
00:32:21,240 --> 00:32:22,520
Er, Miss Rogers.

362
00:32:22,600 --> 00:32:25,040
Elena. Isaac's teacher.

363
00:32:25,120 --> 00:32:26,240
Great. Well...

364
00:32:27,280 --> 00:32:29,920
if you see anything suspicious,
just give us a call.

365
00:32:30,000 --> 00:32:31,920
Straight to mobile,
don't bother with the office.

366
00:32:32,360 --> 00:32:34,440
Oh... er, thank you.

367
00:34:52,600 --> 00:34:54,920
<i>"This is for you," said the kind dog.</i>

368
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:58,440
<i>"Thank you," said Thomas,
"now I don't have to be sad anymore.</i>

369
00:34:58,520 --> 00:35:01,440
As long as I have this,
I will think of you,

370
00:35:01,520 --> 00:35:03,640
<i>and I will never be lonely again."</i>

371
00:35:03,760 --> 00:35:05,920
<i>"Never be lonely again."</i>

372
00:35:50,280 --> 00:35:52,200
What are you doing here, Lucy?

373
00:35:52,320 --> 00:35:53,360
Stocking up.

374
00:35:56,480 --> 00:35:57,680
What are these?

375
00:35:57,800 --> 00:35:59,880
Oh, pain au chocolat.

376
00:36:00,680 --> 00:36:03,120
Don't tell me you've
never had pain au chocolat?

377
00:36:03,160 --> 00:36:04,160
No.

378
00:36:04,280 --> 00:36:07,120
Well, they're nice.
You have them for breakfast.

379
00:36:08,200 --> 00:36:11,440
- Who has chocolate for breakfast?
- You only live once.

380
00:36:12,960 --> 00:36:15,680
- No, you don't.
- Doesn't matter, they're not for you.

381
00:36:17,800 --> 00:36:19,160
Who are they for?

382
00:36:22,440 --> 00:36:23,440
Lucy?

383
00:36:26,760 --> 00:36:28,160
Mum's in the car.

384
00:36:30,880 --> 00:36:34,120
No. No, no, no, no. You can't do this.

385
00:36:34,160 --> 00:36:35,920
She knows this house.

386
00:36:36,000 --> 00:36:38,600
We made memories here,
it's the only place she'll find them.

387
00:36:38,640 --> 00:36:40,160
You are not thinking clearly.

388
00:36:40,200 --> 00:36:44,560
No. No, I'm not because if I don't do
something now, I will lose her forever.

389
00:36:44,640 --> 00:36:46,520
There is no forever.

390
00:36:47,800 --> 00:36:49,520
She will come back.

391
00:36:50,080 --> 00:36:54,120
So will you, so will I,
and so will everyone else.

392
00:36:54,640 --> 00:36:57,760
And round and round
it goes like a fucking pinwheel.

393
00:37:00,360 --> 00:37:05,320
I tried to save her, I tried to
give her a life, but her body rejected it.

394
00:37:06,920 --> 00:37:08,520
There's nothing you can do.

395
00:37:09,480 --> 00:37:11,360
- You don't know that.
- I know everything.

396
00:37:12,880 --> 00:37:15,800
My mind is thousands of years old.

397
00:37:17,080 --> 00:37:20,160
You've got two lives in your head,
I've got hundreds.

398
00:37:21,160 --> 00:37:24,200
I've burnt, I've drowned,
I've bled to death.

399
00:37:24,320 --> 00:37:26,040
I've lived, I've loved.

400
00:37:29,400 --> 00:37:31,640
- I can't help you.
- I'm not asking for your help.

401
00:37:31,760 --> 00:37:34,400
I will come in every day.
I'll feed her, I'll bath her.

402
00:37:34,480 --> 00:37:36,440
- No!
- You won't know she's here.

403
00:37:36,520 --> 00:37:38,200
No, I told you.

404
00:37:38,320 --> 00:37:41,120
You need to stay away from me.
You think you're safe?

405
00:37:42,160 --> 00:37:43,280
You're not.

406
00:37:43,960 --> 00:37:46,120
You think you know me? You don't.

407
00:37:47,040 --> 00:37:48,640
I kill people.

408
00:37:50,520 --> 00:37:53,440
You kill people who hurt others.

409
00:37:53,520 --> 00:37:56,360
I kill people who get in my way.

410
00:38:01,360 --> 00:38:03,000
She won't get in your way.

411
00:38:15,840 --> 00:38:17,600
Excuse me.

412
00:38:19,080 --> 00:38:20,080
Hello.

413
00:38:20,160 --> 00:38:22,960
DI Dhillon.
I think we met last year.

414
00:38:23,640 --> 00:38:24,840
Did we?

415
00:38:24,920 --> 00:38:26,640
The Gideon Shepherd case.

416
00:38:27,480 --> 00:38:28,640
Oh, right.

417
00:38:28,680 --> 00:38:30,400
This is DS Boyd.

418
00:38:30,480 --> 00:38:32,640
We'd like a word with the boss,
if that's alright?

419
00:38:32,680 --> 00:38:35,320
Yeah, sure, wait there.
I'll see if he's free.

420
00:38:38,320 --> 00:38:39,960
<i>No, she's not worked here
for months.</i>

421
00:38:40,640 --> 00:38:43,320
- Are you still in touch?
- Off and on.

422
00:38:43,400 --> 00:38:45,960
She handed her notice after...

423
00:38:46,040 --> 00:38:48,440
- well, everything.
- Where's she working now?

424
00:38:49,320 --> 00:38:50,640
Nowhere.

425
00:38:51,480 --> 00:38:53,360
As far as we know.

426
00:38:54,640 --> 00:38:56,440
What does she do for money?

427
00:38:56,520 --> 00:38:59,000
Well, she had an insurance payout
when her house burnt down,

428
00:38:59,080 --> 00:39:00,936
and she divorced her husband,
he had a bit of cash.

429
00:39:00,960 --> 00:39:02,880
And she's been gambling.

430
00:39:03,840 --> 00:39:05,800
I've seen her at the bookies
a couple of times.

431
00:39:05,880 --> 00:39:06,880
Horse racing?

432
00:39:07,680 --> 00:39:11,080
Wimbledon final. She won a stack of cash.

433
00:39:11,160 --> 00:39:14,840
You don't get great odds on tennis,
so she must've staked quite a bit.

434
00:39:15,640 --> 00:39:18,000
I guess everyone's luck turns eventually.

435
00:39:19,160 --> 00:39:21,816
<i>It's been very difficult
to predict this season, hasn't it?</i>

436
00:39:21,840 --> 00:39:24,320
<i>Most games have been hard to call
so there's every chance</i>

437
00:39:24,400 --> 00:39:26,560
<i>- Kevin will surprise you.
- You're right.</i>

438
00:39:26,640 --> 00:39:30,040
<i>They've made a comeback after
a challenging start to the competition.</i>

439
00:39:30,120 --> 00:39:32,160
<i>Last five weeks
seen a fair few near misses.</i>

440
00:39:33,400 --> 00:39:36,800
<i>The last two games have surprised me.
They've taken on some tough opponents.</i>

441
00:39:36,880 --> 00:39:39,000
<i>Their new coach has
really proved himself.</i>

442
00:39:48,480 --> 00:39:49,560
Ravi.

443
00:39:49,640 --> 00:39:50,640
Hi.

444
00:39:51,440 --> 00:39:53,200
- What are you...?
- I, um...

445
00:39:53,320 --> 00:39:56,600
I'm back in town.
Thought we should catch up.

446
00:39:56,640 --> 00:39:58,400
And I don't have your number, so...

447
00:40:01,760 --> 00:40:03,280
How did you find us?

448
00:40:04,200 --> 00:40:05,640
Well, I'm a detective.

449
00:40:09,560 --> 00:40:12,000
- If it's a bad time, I could just...
- No, it's, er...

450
00:40:12,080 --> 00:40:14,320
It's good to see you.

451
00:40:17,440 --> 00:40:19,960
Hello, Isaac. Long time no see.

452
00:40:28,160 --> 00:40:29,760
Hey. You remembered.

453
00:40:31,000 --> 00:40:33,920
Um, Isaac, do you wanna
change out of your uniform, yeah?

454
00:40:34,000 --> 00:40:35,280
Good boy.

455
00:40:37,640 --> 00:40:40,120
It's a weird place to live, Chambers.

456
00:40:41,840 --> 00:40:43,440
Yeah, well...

457
00:40:44,280 --> 00:40:49,040
I haven't paid my TV license,
so hoping they don't find us out here.

458
00:40:49,760 --> 00:40:52,160
Well, your secret's safe with me.

459
00:40:53,800 --> 00:40:55,200
Do you wanna come in?

460
00:40:58,360 --> 00:41:01,160
Do you want a beer? Or are you on duty?

461
00:41:01,840 --> 00:41:02,920
Sort of.

462
00:41:04,480 --> 00:41:05,680
Sort of?

463
00:41:06,520 --> 00:41:08,520
You're back for him, aren't you?
I saw the news.

464
00:41:09,960 --> 00:41:11,520
I thought it was over.

465
00:41:12,440 --> 00:41:13,640
I thought...

466
00:41:14,160 --> 00:41:17,600
all that stuff he said about
razor blades and resetting...

467
00:41:18,320 --> 00:41:20,080
- maybe he just...
- Slashed his wrists?

468
00:41:21,960 --> 00:41:23,560
Oh, sorry. Sorry.

469
00:41:26,320 --> 00:41:28,080
How long are you back for?

470
00:41:28,760 --> 00:41:30,120
As long as it takes.

471
00:41:31,640 --> 00:41:33,640
I spoke to Isaac's teachers.

472
00:41:33,680 --> 00:41:36,440
They're, er...
they're taking it seriously.

473
00:41:37,880 --> 00:41:40,760
He's left us alone for a year.

474
00:41:40,840 --> 00:41:44,560
He's a deranged monster,
and he's obsessed with you.

475
00:41:45,600 --> 00:41:48,080
He was spotted in the park
behind Isaac's school.

476
00:41:48,160 --> 00:41:49,280
Aren't you worried?

477
00:41:49,360 --> 00:41:51,640
Mmm, should I be?

478
00:41:53,200 --> 00:41:56,360
He's never hurt me,
he's never threatened me.

479
00:41:56,440 --> 00:41:59,000
Yeah, well, he beat me
half to death, so...

480
00:42:04,600 --> 00:42:07,120
I, um...

481
00:42:07,160 --> 00:42:09,160
I keep a taser in the car now.

482
00:42:12,880 --> 00:42:14,520
Is that allowed?

483
00:42:15,600 --> 00:42:16,600
Not really.

484
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:27,760
I tried to visit you in hospital.

485
00:42:30,280 --> 00:42:31,280
Tried?

486
00:42:32,120 --> 00:42:34,320
The boss said it was a bad idea.

487
00:42:34,400 --> 00:42:36,160
I was fighting to keep my job.

488
00:42:38,320 --> 00:42:39,400
Oh.

489
00:42:42,160 --> 00:42:47,000
I did call after,
but you changed your number.

490
00:42:48,680 --> 00:42:51,400
Downgraded. Digital detox.

491
00:42:51,480 --> 00:42:52,560
Smart.

492
00:42:53,520 --> 00:42:55,000
Nope, that's the point.

493
00:42:58,400 --> 00:43:01,400
You should stay for dinner.
Made a... a cassoulet.

494
00:43:01,480 --> 00:43:03,200
Or casserole. What's the different?

495
00:43:03,320 --> 00:43:06,080
What is the difference between
a cassoulet and a casserole?

496
00:43:06,160 --> 00:43:08,920
I just... It's... It's a stew thing.

497
00:43:09,000 --> 00:43:10,800
I don't want to intrude.

498
00:43:10,880 --> 00:43:12,320
No, I've made loads.

499
00:43:14,120 --> 00:43:17,320
Plus, you know,
if you're worried about us,

500
00:43:17,400 --> 00:43:20,680
you probably should stick around a bit,
you know, keep us safe.

501
00:43:21,280 --> 00:43:23,000
I don't think you need me
to keep you safe.

502
00:43:23,080 --> 00:43:24,880
I do need you.

503
00:43:27,160 --> 00:43:31,200
Besides, it's like you said,
there's a monster on the loose.

504
00:43:35,840 --> 00:43:39,000
You don't have to eat it all.
I probably gave you too much.

505
00:43:39,880 --> 00:43:41,840
Not possible. This is delicious.

506
00:43:42,720 --> 00:43:44,256
Well, you're lucky
you're getting real food.

507
00:43:44,280 --> 00:43:46,240
We usually rely on Captain Birdseye,

508
00:43:46,320 --> 00:43:48,800
or Colonel Sanders,
if I'm feeling really stretched.

509
00:43:50,400 --> 00:43:52,640
Clearly have a thing
about men with beards.

510
00:43:58,840 --> 00:44:01,160
Isaac prefers fish fingers, don't you?

511
00:44:02,840 --> 00:44:05,240
Not a big fan of Brussels sprouts, I see.

512
00:44:07,160 --> 00:44:08,480
Top tip:

513
00:44:08,560 --> 00:44:10,920
They're much nicer if you roast them.

514
00:44:11,600 --> 00:44:13,600
If you boil them, they go a bit stodgy.

